[SN]TITLE[SN]
Sticky disc makes any watch a smartwatch

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A gadget that promises to turn almost any regular watch into a smartwatch is being developed in the US.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
4 December 2015 Last updated at 00:01 GMT
The Chronos pad can light up and vibrate when your smartphone receives new messages or calls.
It is expected to cost $99 (Â£66) when it goes on sale in 2016, making it less expensive than an integrated smartwatch.
However the device does not have a screen or voice control as found on most fully-featured devices.
The company's co-founder Mark Nichol told BBC technology reporter Chris Foxx he had focused on including the most 'critical' functionality.
